SIMPLE: cut-out
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cut-out
<hw>Cut"-out`</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧t"out`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Telegraphy)</fld> <def>A species of switch for
changing the current from one circuit to another, or for shortening a
circuit.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A device for
breaking or separating a portion of circuit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something cut out from another object, especially a
piece of thick paper or cardboard with a picture on it (as of a person
or other object), embedded in a larger sheet of paper and having
perforations around the edges of the figure to allow easy removal from
the larger sheet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A valve in the exhaust system of an internal
combustion engine which, when activated, permits the exhaust gases to
bypass the muffler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cut-price</ent>⟦br⟧
